	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" ID="Table6">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=293948">Thurgadin</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Pick Sharpening for the nutcase</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Pick Sharpening for the nutcase</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=298814"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:">Kainis Dragonhawk, Steel Templars, Tarrew Marr</a> | 
		                        12/10/2000 2:33:43 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">in the lower parts of the mine in thurgadin you will see a dwarf staring at some velium.  Hail him and he will respond, but nothing in brackets, ask him <I>"what mine"</I> and he will mention the velium talking to him and giving him secrets, ask him <I>"what secrets"</I> and he will ask you to do him a favor, ask <I>"what favor"</I> and he gives you a pick to sharpen, give it to Harkon along with a small piece of velium and you will get a sharpened axe, which you return to Normon and get a velium focus, no drop, lore, magic and Normon tells you how to talk to velium like he does (hence the nutcase part)
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="2">
