	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				*Taken from EQMaps.com*<BR>
This should help out in what the quest is all about.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Talk to Normon Stonetooth, a coldain who can be found deep in the mines within Thurgadin. He will say that he has a great secret to tell you, but first he needs a favor done. Tell him &quot;I will do a favor&quot;, he will hand you a pick axe and tell you to get Harkon to sharpen it. Harkon can be found at the weapon shop, Scar's Edge. Tell him &quot;Stonetooth sent me&quot; and he will tell you that if you give him a Chunk of Velium, he'll sharpen the axe for you. Hand Hakon the Pick Axe and a Small Block of Velium and you will be rewarded with a new Pick Axe. <BR>
<BR>
Now head back to the mines and hand this new axe to Normon and he will hand you the Velium Focus. He will then tell you to bring the item to Phenocryst, a named Geonid in the Wakening Land [-3200, -400]. Hand him the Velium Focus and he will tell you about the prophecy. Say &quot;How can i help you?&quot; and he will respond by telling you that you must find others like us. Head off to the Crystal Cavers now and deep inside there is a section with many Geonids. Hand the focus to one of the Geonids, doesn't matter which one, and you'll receive it back, though a bit altered. Now head back to the Wakening Land and hand it to Phenocryst. He will tell you that you must find someone, respond with &quot;find what&quot; and he will tell you that a menhir must be constructed to amplify the voices of the Geonids. He will then tell you that he will need three crystals, one Beryl, one Stibnite, and one Iron. He will then also hand you the Elbaite Focus, which has 5 charges of Identify on it. <BR>
<BR>
The Beryl Crystal (Reddish Crystal) can be found in Split Paw, on the floor [0,0]. The Stibnite Crystal (Bent Metallic Crystal) is located in the Great Divide in the wurm caves. In one of the rooms you'll see a patch of blue crystals, behind is where the stibnite can be found, on the ground. The last crystal, Iron (Heavy Metallic Crystal), can be found in the Burning Woods sitting beside a meteor near Slixin Klex. Now return all three crystals and the focus back to Phenocryst and he will hand you back an Azurite Focus. He will then tell you that the ones of flesh are coming, and that you must defeat all three of them. <BR>
<BR>
Now start tracking and you should be able to locate two &quot;Accolyte of Zek&quot;, and a &quot;Bloodpriest Loukond&quot;. Kill the two giants first as most npc's will aggro them and ruin your quest. Once they are dead, loot the corpses and then head out to kill the bloodpriest. On all three corpses you should have found a Holy Symbol of Zek. Hand these three symbols and your new Focus, back to Phenocryst and you will be rewarded with the Phenocryst's Focus.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
